    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I recently came across the `api` keyword when using cython, but it seems that this keyword is not well documented in the docs. \r\nIt is clearly documented how to provide basic wrappings from `cpp`-> `cython` however not the otherway around, i.e. how can a cython extension be made accessible to cpp? The `api` keywords generates `[name]_api.h' and `[name].h` however it is not entirely clear to me how to use it. \r\n\r\nFor example:\r\n\r\n```cython\r\ncdef api class A [object a, type a_t]:\r\n    def __init__(self, int a = 1):\r\n        self.a = a\r\n```\r\n\r\n```cpp\r\n\r\n#include \"A.h\"\r\n#include \"A_api.h\"\r\n#include <iostream>\r\nusing namespace std;\r\n\r\nint main(){\r\n  import_A();\r\n}\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nFails with compilation ` g++ -I ~/miniconda3/include/python3.8 -O2 main.cpp -o test  && ./test`\r\n\r\n```output\r\nmain.cpp:(.text.startup+0x27): undefined reference to `PyImport_ImportModule'\r\n/usr/bin/ld: main.cpp:(.text.startup+0x42): undefined reference to `PyObject_GetAttrString'\r\n/usr/bin/ld: main.cpp:(.text.startup+0x5d): undefined reference to `PyDict_GetItemString'\r\n/usr/bin/ld: main.cpp:(.text.startup+0x78): undefined reference to `PyCapsule_IsValid'\r\n/usr/bin/ld: main.cpp:(.text.startup+0x8f): undefined reference to `PyCapsule_GetPointer'\r\n/usr/bin/ld: main.cpp:(.text.startup+0xb9): undefined reference to `PyObject_GetAttrString'\r\n/usr/bin/ld: main.cpp:(.text.startup+0x144): undefined reference to `PyOS_snprintf'\r\n/usr/bin/ld: main.cpp:(.text.startup+0x153): undefined reference to `PyErr_WarnEx'\r\n/usr/bin/ld: main.cpp:(.text.startup+0x171): undefined reference to `_Py_Dealloc'\r\n/usr/bin/ld: main.cpp:(.text.startup+0x17e): undefined reference to `_Py_Dealloc'\r\n/usr/bin/ld: main.cpp:(.text.startup+0x191): undefined reference to `PyExc_TypeError'\r\n/usr/bin/ld: main.cpp:(.text.startup+0x1a2): undefined reference to `PyErr_Format'\r\n/usr/bin/ld: main.cpp:(.text.startup+0x1b2): undefined reference to `PyExc_ValueError'\r\n/usr/bin/ld: main.cpp:(.text.startup+0x1c9): undefined reference to `PyErr_Format'\r\n/usr/bin/ld: main.cpp:(.text.startup+0x1d3): undefined reference to `PyCapsule_GetName'\r\n/usr/bin/ld: main.cpp:(.text.startup+0x1de): undefined reference to `PyModule_GetName'\r\n/usr/bin/ld: main.cpp:(.text.startup+0x1e5): undefined reference to `PyExc_TypeError'\r\n/usr/bin/ld: main.cpp:(.text.startup+0x207): undefined reference to `PyErr_Format'\r\n/usr/bin/ld: main.cpp:(.text.startup+0x214): undefined reference to `PyModule_GetName'\r\n/usr/bin/ld: main.cpp:(.text.startup+0x21b): undefined reference to `PyExc_ImportError'\r\n/usr/bin/ld: main.cpp:(.text.startup+0x233): undefined reference to `PyErr_Format'\r\n/usr/bin/ld: warning: creating DT_TEXTREL in a PIE\r\ncollect2: error: ld returned 1 exit status\r\n```",
