            "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
            "body": "I'm not 100% sure if/how `test_x` is supposed to be exposed. If it isn't possible then it should probably alert you. They easiest workaround is to create a caller function:\r\n\r\n```\r\ncdef public A_test_x(A a, float x):\r\n    a.test_x(x)\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis does appear in the header.\r\n\r\nHowever, support questions are better directed to https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/cython-users",
